The Hawks have arrested officials at the Free State Lengau Testing and Traffic Centre as part of a sting operation. Courtesy #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - The Hawks have arrested 18 officials at the Free State Lengau Testing and Traffic Centre on Wednesday as part of a sting operation. Authorities are investigating a fraudulent car registration and licensing syndicate across four provinces. READ: Protesters call for end to 'Hollywood-style' arrests by the Hawks Suspects have been arrested in connection with fraud, corruption and money laundering.